cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the delineation of line patterns in images. The use of trainable B-COSFIRE filters, which are a model of some neurons in area V1 of the primary visual cortex, also suggests a focus on computer vision. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category as the B-COSFIRE filters are trainable and configurable. The use of machine learning techniques to automatically configure the filters also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the detection of specific patterns in images.
